</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Cable Crossover Reverse Fly Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Set the cable pulley to a low setting.</li>



<li>Attach a single handle to each pulley.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Stand in the middle of the cable machine.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Grab the left pulley with your right hand and the right pulley with your left hand.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Take a big step back and hinge at the hips so your torso is parallel to the ground.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Cross the cables in front of you.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Extend your arms in front of your chest with the elbows slightly bent.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Inhale as you pull your arms back to shoulder height with a flying motion.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Pause on top.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Exhale as you return to the starting position and bring your arms down towards the floor.</li>



<li>Repeat for the desired number of reps.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips&nbsp;</h4>



<ul>
<li>Maintain a straight back and braced core, avoiding rounding.</li>



<li>Hinge at the hip so your torso is parallel to the ground; do not squat!</li>



<li>Pause briefly at the top position, squeezing your shoulder blades together.</li>



<li>Engage the rear delts and upper back muscles as you pull.</li>



<li>Keep your elbows soft.</li>
</ul>



