<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Cable-Seated-Row">Cable Seated Row</h3>



<p>This <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/seated-cable-row" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">cable seated row</a> variation typically uses a narrow grip with a V-handle attachment and palms facing each other. It focuses more on the rear delts, rhomboid, middle back, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK448120/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">latissimus dorsi, </a>and biceps. Therefore, this variation is better to build more mid-back and arm strength.</p>



<p>Training the back and rear shoulders helps balance the focus on the chest and front shoulder muscles. This can reduce<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC10065112/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow"> tightness in the chest muscles, strengthen the lats, </a>and prevent rounding of the shoulders. Ultimately, this can lead to a more balanced physique.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
