<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Set the cable machine pulley at a high position.</li>



<li>Attach a straight bar to it.</li>



<li>Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing the column bar.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Grip the bar with both hands, palms facing down, and take a big step back from the pulley.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Keep your back straight and lead slightly forward by hinging at your hips.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Inhale and pull the bar down to your chest by bending the elbows.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Exhale and slowly return to the starting position.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Repeat for the desired sets and reps.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your knees soft throughout the exercise.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Keep your back neutral, your chest tall, and your abdomen braced.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Pull the shoulder blades down and back as you pull the handle down.</li>



<li>Keep your elbows pointed down, bringing them down by your side.&nbsp;</li>



<li>The bar should move in a straight path.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Pull until the bar reaches the top of your chest, just below the chin.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Avoid bending the wrist. Keep it straight at all times.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Avoid swinging the weight, and control the movement.</li>
</ul>



